pxnodes.name: Campaign
pxnodes.description: The campaign provides the player with an introduction to the game. In eight missions, the player will learn about most systems, such as providing for their citizens, the interplays of the occident and the orient, and also military conflict. The player sees a captivating story unfold in front of their eyes with convincing characters and their personality, ideals, and flaws.

pxnodes.name: Mission I — A Declaration Of Faith
pxnodes.description: In this mission, the player is introduced to the Emperor's cousin, Lord Richard Northburgh. The Lord is currently building an Emperor's Cathedral in his city Cathedral City to hope for God's assistance in the recovery of the Emperor. Lord Richard Northburgh acts as a mentor for the player and teaches them the basics of the game, while also asking for assistance in building the Cathedral. As the Lord has a much more prestigious city compared to the player, the Lord makes a great impression on the player and acts not just as a mentor, but also as a goal for what the player wants to achieve in their own playthroughs.

pxnodes.name: Mission II — In the Sign of the Cross
pxnodes.description: Continuing with the player's settlement in Mission 1, Lord Richard Northburgh assists the player in advancing the player's settlement. The player learns how to upgrade their peasants to the next level, the citizen level, how to manoeuvre multiple ships, and how to settle more islands. The player is also introduced to Guy Forcas, Marie d'Artois, and Brother Hilarius. The former is sent by Kardinal Lucius to start a crusade against the orient, with Marie d'Arois supporting the cause by delivering war ships and materials to it. While this mission introduces the player to more mechanics, Guy Forcas especially plays a big role in driving the player to complete the missions as fast as possible.

pxnodes.name: Mission III — Departure for the Promised Land
pxnodes.description: Still continuing the settlement of the previous two missions, the player gets to assist the Kardinal personally for the last preparations of the crusade. The player gets introduced to more mechanics, such as trade routes and natural resources, while making sure that the player's population remains satisfied. Lord Richard Northburgh in the meantime questions why the Emporer, while being sick, would allow such a crusade. Lord Richard Northburgh helps the player less, as he needs to assist the crusade as well and can not spare any more resources. He also mentions that the Cathedral's building time is heavily delayed. The Kardinal and Guy Forcas are not transparent at all and the player gets an eerie feeling whenever they interact with Lucius or Guy. Finishing the mission, the Lord approaches the player and tells them that he heard something quite disturbing about it all, leaving the player questioning what he means.

pxnodes.name: Mission IV — The Lost Children
pxnodes.description: The mission starts with Lord Richard Northburgh telling the player that the ships they have been following have children on board and that Corsair ships are taking the children on board. With damaged ships due to a storm, they can not continue following and therefore set sail to a nearby small settlement of the Lord's. The player is first tasked with building a repair crane to repair both of their ships, which means building a thriving settlement. This mission also introduces the orient settlements to the player. Nomads inhibit these islands and have substantially different needs compared to the inhabitants of the occident. Oriental islands also provide different fertilities and resources, which the player has to make use of not just to satisfy the inhabitants of the orient, but also advance from citizens to patricians, which is required toward the end of the mission. The mission introduces the player to naval battles to rescue the children. The missions ends with Guy Forcas and his massive fleet approaching and arresting the Lord. While Guy Forcas tells the player to not play any part in the upcoming crusade, the Lord asks the player to stop the impending war.

pxnodes.name: Mission V — A Storm Breaks Out
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir, the Grand Vizier, acts as the player's mentor in this mission. However, Marie d'Artois has arrived with her massive fleet and starts attacking the Grand Vizier as part of the crusade. The player has to continue developing their settlement from Mission IV in order to support the Grand Vizier in defending himself from the ruthless attacks of Marie d'Artois and Guy Forcas. Over the course of the mission the player has to find multiple artifacts in order to show Marie d'Artois that this crusade is paid for by trafficking children. After showing her the evidence, she stops assisting in the crusade, but Guy Forcas will retaliate. The mission ends when the player destroys Guy Forcas' fleet on his island with Kardinal Lucius arriving. He wants to take revenge and a heavily wounded Marie d'Artois tells the player to set sail to a nearby island of hers to take shelter from the Kardinal's incoming attack.

pxnodes.name: Mission VI — Caught in a Trap
pxnodes.description: Compared to the previous missions, this mission shifts the player's focus completely. Instead of focusing on fulfilling the inhabitant's needs, the player has to secure the survival of Marie d'Artois' inhabitants. Marie tells the player that her other islands secure the needs of the main island, and the player has to focus on training soldiers to defend the island from Lucius' incoming attack. With an ever-increasing number of soldiers landing on the island, more and more sabotage acts by Lucius on the island, and the inhabitants getting more stressed by the situation, this mission constantly puts the player under much stress to ensure the survival of the city. After enduring multiple waves of attacks, Marie d'Artois, who is still heavily injured from the previous mission, asks the player to send a ship to ask for the Grand Vizier's assistance. The mission ends with the Grand Vizier arriving at the island, providing a safe passage for the player and the inhabitants of the city, and leaving behind a furious Kardinal who sets the city ablaze.

pxnodes.name: Mission VII — The man with the mask
pxnodes.description: After fleeing Marie d'Artois' island from the constant attacks of Kardinal Lucius, she and the player arrive in Al Zahir's safe haven in the orient. After hearing about the current situation on one of her islands from Phillipe Lamour, she leaves the player and the other people with Al Zahir and returns to face the Kardinal until the player found a cure for the Emperor in order to stop Lucius. This mission introduces the player to the rest of the oriental buildings and the second and also last civilization level in the orient, Envoys. While trying to find and procure the cure, the player has to interact with multiple neutral factions, such as Heketa the Witch, Izmir the Alchemist, and Al Rashid the Assassin. During the mission, the player also finds Lord Richard Northburgh and saves him from his current imprisonment. The mission finishes with the player procuring the medicine for the Emperor and Phillipe Lamour hastily arriving, informing the Lord and the player that Marie d'Artois is close to defeat and needs their support as soon as possible. Hoping for his fast recovery, Lord Richard Northburgh and the player sail towards Falconstone and Cathedral City, where Lucius is reported to reside at the moment, to stop Lucius' ill-willed plans.

pxnodes.name: Mission VIII — Pillars of Justice
pxnodes.description: After a long ship trip, the player accompanied by the Lord arrive at Falconstone, where the Lord notes that everything the player has built is turned to ash by the Kardinal. The situation is not much better in Cathedral City, but nonetheless the Lord asks the player to finish his project in building the Imperial Cathedral before Kardinal Lucius, who is also intent on proving his faith to God by finishing the Imperial Cathedral before the player. Cathedral City and the other islands around it provide the player with everything to build a blossoming metropolis, however, the constant threat of Kardinal Lucius finishing parts of the cathedral before the player puts pressure on the player during every step they make. Everything the player has learned during the Campaign culminates in this mission. The player not only needs to satisfy the needs of their occidental settlement, but also build an oriental settlement while stopping the Kardinal's sabotages throughout the mission. When the player finishes the Imperial Cathedral before the player, the Emperor and his massive war fleet arrives just in time and he asks the player to bring him the traitorous Lucius, who reportedly has left his city. The mission finishes with the Emperor thanking the player for curing him of his illness and stopping the crusade from claiming more lives. Lord Richard Northburgh, Marie d'Artois, the Grand Vizier Al Zahir, and a just-arriving Sultan thank the player for their commitment to the cause.

pxnodes.name: Easy Difficulty Setting
pxnodes.description: When the player selects the easy difficulty for the missions, the base goods at the start of each mission are more. Also, the player gets the full build costs refunded if they decide to destroy a building they built, therefore the game is very forgiving when the player makes mistakes.

pxnodes.name: Medium Difficulty Setting
pxnodes.description: When the player selects the medium difficulty for the missions, the base goods at the start of each mission are average. The player gets half the build costs refunded if they decide to destroy a building they built, allowing the player to recover decently from mistakes while also being punished slightly.

pxnodes.name: Hard Difficulty Setting
pxnodes.description: When the player selects the hard option for the missions, the base goods at the start of each mission are sparse. Also, the player gets no build costs refunded if they decide to destroy a building they built, punishing the player for mistakes severely.

pxnodes.name: The Emperor's Seal Bearer
pxnodes.description: The player has to select Lord Richard Northburgh's Flagship to administer the player's oath of loyalty to the Emperor before gaining access to the island.

pxnodes.name: Profession of Faith
pxnodes.description: This is the victory condition of the mission. The player has to build a chapel with multiple peasant buildings in its influence radius.

pxnodes.name: The heart of the Settlement
pxnodes.description: The player has to select their marketplace and gather information of their population.

pxnodes.name: Safe as Houses
pxnodes.description: The player is tasked with building three peasant buildings, slowly growing their settlement.

pxnodes.name: Among Crates and Shelves
pxnodes.description: In this mission, the player has to click on the warehouse in order to get information on the current stock levels.

pxnodes.name: The essential Building material
pxnodes.description: Building houses requires wood and currently, the island does not cut down any trees! Lord Richard Northburgh therefore tasks the player with constructing two lumberjacks, emphasizing the need to connect the lumberjacks to a warehouse in order to collect the goods.

pxnodes.name: War on hunger
pxnodes.description: The population might become hungry, as there are no fisherman's huts in Falconstone! Lord Richard Northburgh tasks the player with constructing one on Falconstone's beach.

pxnodes.name: Helper in times of need
pxnodes.description: The player's supply of tools has run low, however, Lord Richard Northburgh allows the player to buy three tons of tools for 150g from him.

pxnodes.name: Help among friends
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh has no ship at Falconstone's harbor, therefore, he asks the player to come to Cathedral City and buy some tools there.

pxnodes.name: Wood for the Imperial cathedral
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh is short on wood and notices the woodcutters on the player's island. He therefore asks the player to assist him and provide 10t of wood for the next step of building the Imperial cathedral.

pxnodes.name: A floating gift
pxnodes.description: As a thank you, Lord Richard Northburgh allows the player to take control of a small trade ship provided by him. The player has to click on it in order to take control.

pxnodes.name: With Sextant and Spy-glass I
pxnodes.description: It looks like one of Lord Richard Northburgh's presents to the player went overboard when they left for Cathedral City. He asks the player to sail to the goods and collect them by clicking on it.

pxnodes.name: With Sextant and Spy-glass II
pxnodes.description: Having collected the tools, the Lord tells the player to sail back to Falconstone and transfer the tools to the city.

pxnodes.name: Fish on the table
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh has a second island nearby where his people produce building materials for the Imperial cathedral. It seems like they are hungry and the player is tasked with delivering 10t of fish to that island.

pxnodes.name: Check the Storage
pxnodes.description: This mission aims to assist the player to see whether they already have enough fish in their warehouse or not.

pxnodes.name: To Work!
pxnodes.description: This quest helps the player to deliver the fish to the island. It tasks the player with transferring 10t of fish from the island's warehouse to their ship.

pxnodes.name: A worthy outcome
pxnodes.description: Motivated by the delivery of fish, the stonemasons present the player with an intricately carved masonry to be used at the construction site of the Imperial cathedral. The stonemasons ask the player to deliver the masonry to Cathedral City as soon as possible.

pxnodes.name: The missing Cargo
pxnodes.description: While sailing around the map, Lord Richard Northburgh draws the player's attention to some flotsam. He makes it out as missing cargo for the construction site and asks the player to deliver it to his city.

pxnodes.name: More Peasant houses
pxnodes.description: In order to provide housing for more than 90 peasants, the player has to construct six more peasant houses.

pxnodes.name: Averting danger
pxnodes.description: Thinking about a way to avoid similar accidents, Lord Richard Northburgh asks the player to map out the two reefs in the vicinity. When the ship is close to a reef, it will start to scout the reef and produce a map that can be taken to Cathedral city.

pxnodes.name: Where is the Master builder?
pxnodes.description: When clicking on the construction site of the Imperial cathedral, Lord Northburgh notices that the master builder is currently missing. The Lord asks you to find him in the city.

pxnodes.name: In the name of the Cross
pxnodes.description: This is the overall goal of the mission - Guy Forcas requires you to assist him in preparing for the crusade.

pxnodes.name: Supply the Crusader army
pxnodes.description: Guy Forcas needs 15t of Fish and 3t of Cider, as the army is getting hungry and thirsty.

pxnodes.name: The Market building
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh advises the player to start expanding their settlement and start the production of cider to keep up with Guy Forcas' ever-increasing demands. In order to build the cider farm, the Lord mentions to extend the construction radius by placing down a market building.

pxnodes.name: Cool drinks
pxnodes.description: Once the market house is built, the player can place their Cider farm.

pxnodes.name: A searching look
pxnodes.description: Something seems off, as the cider farm does not produce anything. The player is tasked to left-click the production building.

pxnodes.name: To work!
pxnodes.description: When looking at the production rate of the building, the player notices that the production rate is 0%! This is because the cider farm requires fields. The player can either use the "Cultivate"-button or "Create Fields"-button to place all fields automatically by the game or place each field manually.

pxnodes.name: Ready for collection
pxnodes.description: Last but not least, as required with almost all production buildings, they need to be connected by road to a market building.

pxnodes.name: A messenger from the War
pxnodes.description: Guy Forcas asks you to deliver a letter to Marie d'Artois. She has a settlement close to Falconstone and has to fulfil her duty to the Emperor. Lord Richard Northburgh asks you to read the letter by clicking on it—the decision is up to the player to do so or not.

pxnodes.name: Weapon belt and Lances
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois ordered weapons at the Lord's and asks you to retrieve the crate of weapons from his island.

pxnodes.name: Rescue at Sea
pxnodes.description: While delivering the first war ship to the army, it runs against a reef and the ship gets damaged. The player is tasked with delivering wood 10t of wood to repair the ship.

pxnodes.name: The Feast
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh's workers are constantly working due to Guy Forcas' demands and the Lord complains that the cathedral construction had to stop. In order to keep spirits high, the Lord asks the player to deliver 10t of fish to the workers in order to boost their morale.

pxnodes.name: In new Garments
pxnodes.description: The army requires new clothes! Guy Forcas orders you to start producing linen garments.

pxnodes.name: Finest Weaving
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh tells the player that they need to build a weaver that uses hemp to produce linen garments. Depending on the player's city, they might need to first upgrade peasant housing to citizen housing.

pxnodes.name: The Hemp plantation
pxnodes.description: The weaver requires hemp to weave. Once again it requires fields to work and, if placed in the influence radius of the Weaver's hut, the workers of the Weaver's hut can go get the resources themselves and the Hemp plantation does not require a road connection to the warehouse.

pxnodes.name: A second Plantation
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh mentions that one Weaver's hut requires the input of two Hemp plantations in order to function well, so the player is tasked with building a second Hemp plantation.

pxnodes.name: Unwilling volunteers
pxnodes.description: In this optional mission, Guy Forcas asks the player to recruit knights in Falconstone. This is the first mission where the player has to find people on an island, introducing them to this kind of mission type.

pxnodes.name: Transfer of Soldiers
pxnodes.description: Once the knights are found, Guy Forcas, who is a little bit put off by the quality of the knights, requires the player to deliver them to him.

pxnodes.name: Rope teams
pxnodes.description: Resources for ships and war machines are running low, so Guy Forcas asks the player to deliver 5t of ropes to his shipyard.

pxnodes.name: The Ropeyard
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh assists the player in constructing the required buildings to fulfil Guy Forcas' request for ropes. In this mission, he asks the player to construct a ropeyard.

pxnodes.name: Supply the Ropeyard
pxnodes.description: Similar to the Weaver's hut, the Ropeyard also requires hemp to produce ropes. However, the ropeyard only requires one hemp plantation to run at 100% production rate. This combined with the cider plantation gives the player a first insight into the different kinds of production chains.

pxnodes.name: The Crusade swimmers
pxnodes.description: It seems that there are knights that do not want to take part in the crusade and threw themselves over board! Guy Forcas wants you to find the cowards and bring them to him without hesitation.

pxnodes.name: Monk sought
pxnodes.description: This mission requires the player to settle a new island and then bring the monastery into their influence area.

pxnodes.name: Land seizure
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh helps the player in settling on the new island. The player has to load wood and tools on the ship, sail to the island's coast and then build a warehouse on the island.

pxnodes.name: The blessing of the Weapons
pxnodes.description: After constructing the warehouse, Guy Forcas hastily asks the player to bring Brother Hilarius to him. Brother Hilarius does question the reasons for the crusade and all the weapons, but goes along nonetheless.

pxnodes.name: A Harbour for the Crusaders
pxnodes.description: This is the main quest the player has to complete in order to finish the mission. With the arrival of Kardinal Lucius, he gives the player more assignments and is made responsible for building a huge harbor to support the fleet and troops before their departure to the orient.

pxnodes.name: Building begins
pxnodes.description: Before being able to build a harbor, the player is tasked with building a warehouse on an island southwest of Falconstone.

pxnodes.name: Doublets and Tunics
pxnodes.description: After Marie d'Artois announces the first departure of her ships, clicking on her warehouse prompts Marie to say that her knights do not have enough clothing. The player is tasked to deliver 10t of Linen garments to her city,

pxnodes.name: The Harbour master's office
pxnodes.description: Eager to build a big harbor to impress Kardinal Lucius, Guy Forcas asks the player to place a harbour master. This task might be quite difficult for new players, as the harbour master's office requires a new resource—stone.

pxnodes.name: A stony matter
pxnodes.description: Hearing what Guy Forcas asks of the player, Lord Richard Northburgh assists the player in placing their first Stonemason's hut, which requires a natural resource, namely a stone deposit. He also notes that the newly acquired island Hookburgh has such a deposit.

pxnodes.name: The Transport ship
pxnodes.description: Given the player's production of wood, ropes, and stone, the player is tasked to build a new small trade ship.

pxnodes.name: The launch
pxnodes.description: Before the construction of the trading ship, a shipyard has to be built.

pxnodes.name: The important things
pxnodes.description: Instead of manually transporting the stone from Hookburgh to Falconstone, Lord Richard Northburgh tells the player that they can set up automatic transport routes.

pxnodes.name: Provisions for a thousand men
pxnodes.description: Given that the army requires so much proviant, Guy Forcas demands an increase in storage size by upgrading the warehouse in Port Sacral.

pxnodes.name: High demand
pxnodes.description: When visiting Marie d'Artois, she mentions that she needs more wood to produce enough ships, as there are so many crusaders that want to join.

pxnodes.name: Cathedral construction delayed
pxnodes.description: The crusade does not just delay the player, but also Lord Richard Northburgh and the construction of his Imperial cathedral. In order to speed things up, he asks the player to deliver 5t of stone.

pxnodes.name: Bread and circuses
pxnodes.description: Given that the crusaders still need to wait before departing to the orient, Guy Forcas suggests that a tavern in Falconstone might keep the crusader's spirits high.

pxnodes.name: Final preparations
pxnodes.description: Guy Forcas notes that the upgrade of the warehouse in Port Sacral was not satisfactory and therefore demands the player to build four more storehouses, which should suffice in increasing the available storage space.

pxnodes.name: In the service of Guy Forcas
pxnodes.description: Even though the player has been continuously supporting all the crusade's participants, he pressures the player in working faster and asks of more support of the player to prepare for the crusade.

pxnodes.name: A huge responsibility
pxnodes.description: Blinded by the crusade and her visions, Marie d'Artois simply left Inglebeck to burn in ashes. Citizens started leaving the island as they do not believe in her return and Philippe Lamour asks the player to bring Inglebeck back to what it once was by caring for the people still living on the island.

pxnodes.name: Population census
pxnodes.description: Given that the time between Marie d'Artois' departure and the player accepting "A huge responsibility" plays a huge role in the current state of Inglebeck, we want the player to take notice of the current status of Inglebeck by clicking on the marketplace and looking at the inhabitants overview.

pxnodes.name: Naval maneuvers
pxnodes.description: More ships are required to transport all knights to the orient, so the player is tasked with delivering four more small trade ships to Guy Forcas' island.

pxnodes.name: Safety first
pxnodes.description: When arriving at the port, Marie d'Artois notices that one of her ships got damaged on its passage. A harbor for a crusade needs to be able to handle such mishaps, and therefore, Guy Forcas requires the player to build a repair crane.

pxnodes.name: Molten iron
pxnodes.description: Hurriedly, Guy Forcas needs the player to deliver him 10t of iron.

pxnodes.name: Treasure in the Mountain
pxnodes.description: Given that the player has never produced iron up until now, Lord Richard Northburgh assists the player in producing iron. First, he asks the player to construct one iron mine in Hookburgh, as iron requires a natural iron deposit, similar to the stonemason.

pxnodes.name: Hot Iron
pxnodes.description: Raw iron is not good enough to produce tools, so the Lord tasks the player with building an iron smelter close to the iron mine.

pxnodes.name: A fire in the Forge
pxnodes.description: Noting that the iron smelter does not work, Lord Richard Northburgh tells the player that they need to get coal via a charcoal burner's hut. Similar to woodcutters' huts, the charcoal burner requires trees in its vicinity, therefore it has to be placed in the forest without buildings in the vicinity, otherwise its production rate will suffer.

pxnodes.name: Hammer and saw
pxnodes.description: Finally, after procuring the iron necessary, the player can place a Toolmaker's workshop and the production of tools should start rolling.

pxnodes.name: Involuntary service
pxnodes.description: Seeing the toolmaker's workshop, Guy Forcas asks the player to deliver 15t of tools to the crusade.

pxnodes.name: Missing children
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh is devastated by the missing children and can not stop thinking about them. The mission's goal is to find the children and bring them back to safety.

pxnodes.name: Out of the frying pan into the fire
pxnodes.description: The island the player landed on hosts a monastery. The player is tasked with connecting the monastery to contact the monks about the missing children.

pxnodes.name: A first clue
pxnodes.description: Also following the children, the player meets Brother Hilarius in the monastery. He received a clue about the missing children and tasks the player with sailing to the reef northwest of Guelphdon.

pxnodes.name: Shipwreck
pxnodes.description: When approaching the reef northeast of Guelphdon, Lord Richard Northburgh notices a shipwreck with children clinging onto their lives. The player has to order their ship to collect the children.

pxnodes.name: Soaking wet children
pxnodes.description: Brother Hilarius offers the player to provide shelter for the children and asks the player to bring the children to Guelphdon's warehouse.

pxnodes.name: Tattered clothes
pxnodes.description: Brother Hilarius notes that the children's clothes are completely torn apart and asks the player to provide 4t of linen garments for the children.

pxnodes.name: A request for help
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh notes that an advisor of the Sultan, Grand vizier Al Zahir of the orient has a settlement close to Guelphdon and might be able to help them in their pursuit of the children. Therefore, Lord Richard Northburgh asks the player to click on his ship and receive his present.

pxnodes.name: A diplomatic mission
pxnodes.description: The Grand vizier has his island in the south. The player is tasked with setting their ship off to the South and find the Grand vizier's island.

pxnodes.name: Calamity on the high Sea
pxnodes.description: When arriving, Al Zahir notes that one of his ships is damaged. He asks the player to deliver 3t of ropes to the damaged ship.

pxnodes.name: Tools production
pxnodes.description: Similar to the previous mission, the player should produce their own tools, as this way is faster and cheaper than buying tools from the monastery or the Caravanserai.

pxnodes.name: Repair work
pxnodes.description: Due to the storm, both Lord Richard Northburgh's and the player's ships are heavily damaged, which impacts their speed negatively. In order to repair ships, the player can build a repair crane to repair both ships.

pxnodes.name: A home for the children
pxnodes.description: After Al Zahir gives the player control over the damaged ship, Brother Hilarius asks the player to deliver the children to the monastery on Guelphdon so he can look after them.

pxnodes.name: The Road to Karim
pxnodes.description: This quest tasks the player with settling their first island in the orient. Al Zahir suggests that Karim, who runs a Caravanserai in Ku'Raast, might have seen something connected to the missing children. The player needs to settle the island and connect the Caravanserai via road.

pxnodes.name: You scratch my back...
pxnodes.description: Karim hints at him knowing something about the missing children, but there are no people buying stuff at his Caravanserai. He wants the player to construct the first settlement containing at least 145 nomads.

pxnodes.name: The Desert lives
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir notes that nomads have other dietary requirements compared to the occidental inhabitants, also given by the living conditions of the different climate on oriental islands. To make the desert fertile, the people of the orient developed Norias, which Al Zahir suggest the player to build in order to make fertile land.

pxnodes.name: The Date plantation
pxnodes.description: Nomads prefer dates over fish, bread, or the like, and therefore the Grand vizier asks the player to build a date plantation. He reminds the player that the date plantation needs to run on fertile land, therefore, the goal is to build a date plantation with a production rate of at least 50%.

pxnodes.name: Tasty
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh notes that Ku'Raast provides suitable fertilities to produce spices, which is a need of citizens. Once again, the spice farm should run at a production rate of at least 50%.

pxnodes.name: Familiar surroundings
pxnodes.description: Noting the children on Ku'Raast, Brother Hilarius asks the player to bring the children to the island in the North so that Brother Hilarius can take care of the children.

pxnodes.name: A sign of trust
pxnodes.description: Seeing how the player takes care of the missing children and their oriental settlement, the Grand Vizier asks the player to meet him at his island.

pxnodes.name: An important Messenger
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir provides the player with a letter that can be given to the Mine manager in the Southeast. The Mine manager should now be more open to discuss the missing children.

pxnodes.name: Children underground
pxnodes.description: After seeing Al Zahir's letter, the Mine manager tells the player that he did make a deal with The Corsairs to buy some children to work in the mines. However, he still asks the player for 10t of tools, 5t of spices, and 2000 Gold coins in exchange for the children.

pxnodes.name: Free at Last!
pxnodes.description: When taking the children onboard, Brother Hilarius notes the awful state of the children and hurries the player to take the children to the monastery, where he can provide them shelter.

pxnodes.name: Ascension of a Village
pxnodes.description: Given the newly acquired spices, Lord Richard Northburgh argues that the citizen's needs can be satisfied where the island might attract patricians to come live in the city. He challenges the player to fulfil all the civilian's needs to attract patricians.

pxnodes.name: A crust of Bread
pxnodes.description: Noting that the Patricians that just moved in also provide the knowledge to produce Bread, Brother Hilarius inquires whether the player can provide 10t of Bread for the children.

pxnodes.name: A bowl of Milk
pxnodes.description: Given the children's weak state, Brother Hilarius asks the player to provide 15t of Milk to the children.

pxnodes.name: Self-defence
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh notes the increased activity of Corsairs in the vicinity and given the patricians, he advises the player to build a weaponsmith in preparation of dire situations.

pxnodes.name: In pursuit of the Corsairs
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir heard about rumors that the Corsairs might have the children and sends the player to investigate. The player is tasked with finding the Corsair to the Southwest of the region.

pxnodes.name: Al Zahir's help
pxnodes.description: When approached with the topic of missing children, Hassan ben Sahid, the leader of the Corsairs, threatens with attacking the player's ship if they continue to investigate that matter. Al Zahir is enraged by the Corsair's behavior and asks the player to deliver 5t of Weapons to his island. He will provide the player with a Boarding Crew, as a head-on attack could bring the children into danger as well.

pxnodes.name: Prepare to board!
pxnodes.description: Using the newly acquired boarding crew, the Grand vizier asks the player to use the crew and acquire the ship and rescue the children safely.

pxnodes.name: Safe and sound
pxnodes.description: After the successful boarding of the Corsair ship, Brother Hilarius once again offers to provide shelter for the children.

pxnodes.name: Sea battle
pxnodes.description: Apparently there is another group of children held by Hassan ben Sahid in Corsair island. In order to force Hassan ben Sahid to release the last group of children, Lord Richard Northburgh tasks the player with building two more small warships so that the player can start an attack on the Corsair's remaining fleet.

pxnodes.name: Carpet trading
pxnodes.description: Given the current circumstances, Al Zahir also wants to help the player with their attack on Hassan ben Sahid's fleet. In exchange for 3t of Carpets, Al Zahir offers an Oriental warship. This mission also introduces the player to another production chain that can only be built in the Orient.

pxnodes.name: Act of reprisal
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh calls for action and to attack the Corsairs head-on after examining the player's newly built war ships. The player is tasked with destroying all four remaining Corsair ships of Hassan ben Sahid, who just bragged to have brought the last remaining group of children onto Corsair island.

pxnodes.name: Explosion hazard
pxnodes.description: Seemingly having changed his mood, the Mine manager wants to show his better side and offers a great deal to the player: in exchange for 10t of tools and 15t of spices, the Mine manager gives the player a powder keg, that the player can use to blow up all the Corsair's ship in one blow.

pxnodes.name: Saved!
pxnodes.description: After seeing all his remaining ships hit rock bottom, the Corsair agrees to release the children. The player can pick up the last group of missing children at Hassan ben Sahid's island.

pxnodes.name: Forget the terrible experience
pxnodes.description: The last group of children has been picked up and Brother Hilarius urges the player to deliver them as soon as possible to the monastery, so he can look after them.

pxnodes.name: Shoulder to shoulder
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois has arrived and sends out continuous attacks against the Orient and Grand vizier Al Zahir. He asks the player to defend the Orient and stop this crusade once and for all.

pxnodes.name: Relief supplies for Al Zahir
pxnodes.description: Given the recent attacks, Grand vizier Al Zahir had to take in many refugees, who are now waiting in the blazing sun without suitable clothing. Al Zahir begs the player to provide him with 8t of Leather jerkins

pxnodes.name: Leather specialist wanted
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir notes that the player's island, Guelphdon, does not have a person specialized in producing leather jerkins yet. He suggests increasing the number of Patricians so that a leather specialist moves into the city, unlocking the required buildings.

pxnodes.name: Leather jerkin manufacture
pxnodes.description: Once the leather specialist is found, Al Zahir asks the player to construct a complete production chain to produce leather jerkins. A new building type is introduced in this production chain: buildings that require to be built over rivers. Guelphdon does not have a river, so the Grand vizier suggests the player to settle the island to the North.

pxnodes.name: Salvation of the innocent
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois attacks one of Al Zahir's islands, Dar el Marisi. He asks the player for aid in picking up the survivors.

pxnodes.name: Deliver the Date pickers
pxnodes.description: Safe on the ship, the Grand vizier tells the player to stop by his harbour so he can provide shelter for the Date pickers.

pxnodes.name: The eyewitness report
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir needs the war to stop as soon as possible. Therefore, he wrote down all the effects of the crusade on the people and asks the player to take the report to Marie d'Artois' island, as the player is not actively in war with her.

pxnodes.name: The Grand vizier's hope
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir's last hope for a peaceful resolution in this war lie in the letter, so he asks the player to bring the letter to Marie d'Artois as soon as possible.

pxnodes.name: A suspicious wreck
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois' response to the letter is not as hoped. Still looking to protect his people, Al Zahir mentions a suspicious wreck that might have evidence regarding Guy Forcas' shady dealings. The player is tasked with checking the wreck out.

pxnodes.name: The Logbook
pxnodes.description: In the wreckage the player found a logbook, however, the contents are protected with a code. Al Zahir mentions an old colleague of his, Ibn al Hakim, who is the only one that could be able to crack the code. The player has to deliver the logbook to Ibn al Hakim.

pxnodes.name: Support for the refugees
pxnodes.description: Noting the little food supplies left for the refugees, Al Zahir asks the player for supporting the food supply by providing 10t of Dates and 10t of Milk.

pxnodes.name: Risky new beginnings
pxnodes.description: Even though Dar el Marisi had just been attacked by Marie d'Artois, the Grand vizier hopes that the player's settlement might be left alone for the time being. As the requirements for "Support the refugees" requires a settlement to produce dates and milk, the player is tasked with building a small settlement on Dar el Marisi.

pxnodes.name: Small warships
pxnodes.description: Preparing for the worst, Al Zahir urges the player to build three small warships to defend themselves from attacks of Marie d'Artois.

pxnodes.name: The transcription
pxnodes.description: Ibn al Hakim needs wares to transcribe the logbook. He asks the player to provide 5t of Paper and 5t of Indigo.

pxnodes.name: Specialist required
pxnodes.description: Similar to the production of leather jerkins, Al Zahir notes that more Patricians need to move in in order to produce the wares requested by Ibn al Hakim. 940 Patricians suffice.

pxnodes.name: Paper production
pxnodes.description: Paper production requires another spot at the river for the paper mill and indigo.

pxnodes.name: Preservation of knowledge
pxnodes.description: Seemingly out of nowhere, Marie d'Artois' ships start attacking Ibn al Hakim's ships and asks for aid in the battle. There are three waves of attacks that the player has to defend Ibn al Hakim.

pxnodes.name: Send them to the Tower!
pxnodes.description: Brother Hilarius notes that chaos is rising in Guelphdon and the player should try to restore order. He suggests building a Debtor's prison to restore order.

pxnodes.name: Glassworks
pxnodes.description: The Debtor's prison requires glass as its last resource. Brother Hilarius assists the player in constructing a production chain of glass, which requires a smelter, a forest glassworks, and a Quartz mine.

pxnodes.name: Solace in the dark times
pxnodes.description: Brother Hilarius claims that books might provide the people a good distraction from these uncertain times. He asks the player to deliver 10t of Books to Guelphdon.

pxnodes.name: Guy Forcas's secret
pxnodes.description: Convinced that there might be something in the Corsair Strongbox to show Marie d'Artois and stop the crusade, Al Zahir asks the player to bring the Iron Strongbox and a Copper Key to him.

pxnodes.name: The wreck in the desert
pxnodes.description: There are signs in the logbook that one of the ships was washed up on one of the islands to the Southeast.

pxnodes.name: Buried in the sand
pxnodes.description: A storm rages on the island and there are many crates on the island. The player is tasked with searching all five crates on the island to find the Copper key.

pxnodes.name: The wreck on the Pearl reef
pxnodes.description: The logbook also mentions another ship that sunk on a nearby reef. However, it seems like Guy Forcas is also looking for the cargo.

pxnodes.name: Aid from the Orient
pxnodes.description: Preparing for a confrontation at the reef, Al Zahir asks the player to deliver 10t of War machines in exchange for 5 Oriental war ships.

pxnodes.name: Battle at the Pearl reef
pxnodes.description: Guy Forcas is out to destroy the player's ships if they come close to his ships. The player has to sink all his ships in order to access the flotsam with the strongbox.

pxnodes.name: The Strongbox
pxnodes.description: After successfully defeating all of Guy Forcas' ships, Al Zahir urges the player to pick up the flotsam, containing the evidence of Guy Forcas' evildoing.

pxnodes.name: Missing!
pxnodes.description: Missing goat milk deliveries worry Al Zahir and therefore asks the player to look to Wadi al Mûd and whether everything is okay.

pxnodes.name: To arms!
pxnodes.description: When arriving at Wadi al Mûd, the player sees two of Marie d'Artois' small warships attacking the island's warehouse. The player has to destroy the ships before they destroy the warehouse in order to safe the goatherds.

pxnodes.name: Evacuation of refugees
pxnodes.description: Wadi al Mûd is sadly destroyed and Al Zahir wants to provide shelter for the goatherds on his island. He wants the player to provide passage for the refugges.

pxnodes.name: Indisputable evidence
pxnodes.description: After unlocking the strongbox, Al Zahir notes that the Corsair Treaty has enough evidence to show Marie d'Artois the real victims of this crusade. The player is tasked with bringing the evidence to Marie d'Artois' island, Gallowshill.

pxnodes.name: Under the White flag
pxnodes.description: Brother Hilarius hears of the player's plans to sail to Gallowshill and points out that after sinking Marie d'Artois' ships, she will receive the player only by bombarding their ships. A White flag, as provided by Brother Hilarius, might solve that issue.

pxnodes.name: The end of the Crusade
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois notes the White flag and receives the player with the evidence. Completely flabbergasted by the evidence and the revelation, she says that she can not lead this crusade and steps down as general. However, Guy Forcas is quick to react and starts attacking Marie d'Artois' ships, leaving her and the player no chance but to retreat for now. However, in the end, everyone agrees that sinking all of Guy Forcas' ships to stop the constant attacks on the Orient is the new goal.

pxnodes.name: Distress call to the Sultan
pxnodes.description: Given the massive warship fleet of Guy Forcas, Al Zahir prepared a caravel to send to the Sultan in order to ask for aid from the Sultan. The player has to escort the ship safely out of the region.

pxnodes.name: More War machines
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir also offers the player to build more Oriental Warships in exchange for 4t of War machines.

pxnodes.name: The last bastion
pxnodes.description: Kardinal Lucius is set on destroying the player and Marie d'Artois for deserting the Crusade. Marie, who is heavily injured from fleeing in the previous mission, tells the player that defending the Keep in Edenisle is priority number one in order to survive.

pxnodes.name: The first sortie
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois instructs the player in land warfare and orders the player to construct 1 small or large Encampment at the Keep and position it on the island.

pxnodes.name: Command
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois tasks the player with getting to know the troop and clicking on the Encampment.

pxnodes.name: Defending the homeland
pxnodes.description: According to Marie's informants, Kardinal Lucius will land on the Southside of the island. Given the information, Marie asks the player to move 1 Encampment to the Southside of the island, close to the harbour.

pxnodes.name: Mobilisation
pxnodes.description: The Kardinal will attack with many units and Marie asks the player to train at least 2 additional Encampments.

pxnodes.name: Repair work
pxnodes.description: Marie notices huge gaps in the city wall and wants the player to fill the gap between the city gate and the two Watchtowers.

pxnodes.name: Defence from above
pxnodes.description: As a good offense can also provide a good defense, Marie tasks the player with building three Watchtowers or Fortified towers to protect the city. She gives the player the free option to place the towers where the player pleases.

pxnodes.name: Troop supplies
pxnodes.description: Provisions allow the troops to recover hitpoints lost from previous battle faster. Given that Kardinal Lucius will send his troops in waves and the continuous battle, Marie prompts the player to produce 10t of Provisions for the troops.

pxnodes.name: The evacuation
pxnodes.description: Kardinal Lucius and his troops land on Fingal, one of Marie's production islands. Theodore the Peasant asks the player to save him and the other workers before Lucius further takes possession of the island.

pxnodes.name: The search for Theodore's brothers
pxnodes.description: According to Theodore, there are two more ships that left before the invasion but are still missing. The player is tasked with looking for more survivors in the reefs to the North and West of Bushelhill.

pxnodes.name: Escape with difficulties
pxnodes.description: On a deserted island, the player finds the damaged ship of Jacques the Peasant. He asks the player for 10t of Tools and 10t of Ropes so they can repair the ship and leave.

pxnodes.name: In terrible distress
pxnodes.description: Spotted by two of Kardinal Lucius's ships, Yves the Peasant and his People are cornered by these ships. The player is asked to destroy the two ships in order to save the people.

pxnodes.name: The baptism of fire
pxnodes.description: Setting foot on Edenisle, Marie d'Artois calls the player to destroy the first two Encampments of the Kardinal.

pxnodes.name: Fisherman's huts
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois notes that the destruction of the fisherman's huts by Lucius might make her people starve. In order to avoid such a fate, she asks the player to construct three fisherman's huts toward the North of the island.

pxnodes.name: Noble privileges
pxnodes.description: Furious that the player and Marie d'Artois brought the war to Edenisle, they do not even want to think about a war and instead continue living with their luxuries. This mission tasks the player with keeping the number of Noblemen living in the city at at least 333 Noblemen.

pxnodes.name: Iron rations
pxnodes.description: While Encampments are a great way to defend, they are always at risk of losing men as they fight in melee. Trebuchets, which can attack from afar, do not have this problem. However, these require War machines. Marie d'Artois asks the player to construct 2 War machines workshops in order to have enough material to keep on building new military units.

pxnodes.name: Divine visions
pxnodes.description: Marie tells the player that she had a vision that the recently destroyed warehouse should be constructed toward the North side of the island, Especially given that currently there is no way for the supply ships to bring wares to Edenisle.

pxnodes.name: The Cardinal's madness
pxnodes.description: It does not seem like Kardinal Lucius is going to stop his continuing attacks on Edenisle. The player has to survive!

pxnodes.name: Replacing what is lost
pxnodes.description: When the hemp plantations or Cider farms are destroyed by Lucius, Marie will note that these production facilities are required to keep the population happy.

pxnodes.name: Cider farms
pxnodes.description: Three new Cider farms are required to keep the population happy. The Northwest of the island should be safe from further attacks and therefore are a great place to build these.

pxnodes.name: Hemp plantations
pxnodes.description: Three new Hemp plantations are required to keep the population happy. The Northwest of the island should be safe from further attacks and therefore are a great place to build these.

pxnodes.name: The eye of the enemy
pxnodes.description: Marie heard rumours about the Kardinal's spies in the city. The player has to find them fast in order to avoid catastrophe!

pxnodes.name: Meeting the Robber baron
pxnodes.description: Barnabas, the Robber baron, is devasted to what is happening to Marie and demands the player to let him talk to the spies. He will for sure find out whatever they have to say. The player has to build a road to Barnabas' Robber baron castle to do so.

pxnodes.name: In the grip of Barnabas
pxnodes.description: Barnabas, who is also Marie's former instructor, wants the player to hand over the spies.

pxnodes.name: A glimmer of hope
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois notifies the player that she wrote a message to the Grand vizier, Al Zahir, as she does not see any other way of getting out of this situation. She pledges that this is the only way out and begs the player to send an expedition ship to be saved by the Grand vizier from the madness-ridden Kardinal.

pxnodes.name: At the last second
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir arrives at Edenisle's harbor and urges the player and everyone else to come on board fast so that they can successfully get out of this losing fight.

pxnodes.name: Help from on high
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir's information says that the Emperor is somewhere on an island in the North. The player should request an audience to tell the Emperor about Kardinal Lucius' war as soon as possible.

pxnodes.name: Oriental flavour
pxnodes.description: The inhabitants of the player's island require food. The player has to build one Date plantation.

pxnodes.name: The Emperor's cousin
pxnodes.description: Hildegard von Lewenstein informs the player that the Emperor is gravely ill and she does not let anyone get near to the Emperor. She would only make exceptions for close family members. Al Zahir therefore proposes to find the missing Lord Richard Northburgh.

pxnodes.name: Searching for Clues
pxnodes.description: There are three other parties in the region: Izmir, the Alchemist, Hekata, the Witch, and Al Rashid, the Assassin. Maybe they know more?

pxnodes.name: The Barter
pxnodes.description: Hekata does not know anything about Lord Richard Northburgh, but found a message in a bottle. She proposes a trade of the message in the bottle with 5t of Milk.

pxnodes.name: Fresh Goat's milk
pxnodes.description: Noting that the Nomads also want milk, Al Zahir suggests constructing a Goat farm in the player's settlement.

pxnodes.name: The Encryption
pxnodes.description: Noticing the message in the bottle and the weird cipher, Izmir offers his services to decipher the code. The player has to bring the message to warehouse and connect his tower with the player's settlement.

pxnodes.name: Sensational
pxnodes.description: Izmir is on the breakthrough for creating a new invention. He requires 10t of Iron ore and 10t of Gold ore to do so.

pxnodes.name: A daring Plan
pxnodes.description: Abbess Hildegard wants the player to make a map of the Assassin's tower, after finding out that Lord Richard Northburgh is held as prisoner in there. The player requires 6t of Indigo and 5t of Paper to draw up a map.

pxnodes.name: The Map
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir hears of the plan and gives more instructions on how to get the materials requested bu the Abbess. He says that the player can buy the paper at his island and helps the player with building an Indigo plantation.

pxnodes.name: News from Marie
pxnodes.description: Phillipe Lamour has returned to the region with news about Marie's situation: it is dire, but a delivery of 20t of Dates and 20t of Milk might improve her chances of surviving the current battle.

pxnodes.name: Volunteers please!
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir argues that the Assassin's tower is heavily guarded and a secret mission has to be conducted. He argues that with more Envoys living in the city, maybe they can find volunteers capable of conducting such a secret mission to free Lord Richard Northburgh.

pxnodes.name: Noble Knotting
pxnodes.description: In pursuit of reaching the new civilization level of Envoys, Al Zahir assists the player and tells them, that Nomads like to possess carpets to decorate their tents with. He wants the player to have the following buildings: 1 Carpet workshop, 1 Silk plantation, and 1 Indigo farm.

pxnodes.name: Oriental Architecture
pxnodes.description: Nomads and Envoys use Mosaics to build more sophisticated buildings. Therefore, the Grand vizier wants the player to construct the following buildings to produce the more advanced building material: 1 Mosaic workshop, 1 Quartz quarry, and 1 Clay pit.

pxnodes.name: In the name of Allah
pxnodes.description: Nomads want to have a place where they can practice their faith and therefore Al Zahir says that the player should construct a Mosque close to the Nomad houses.

pxnodes.name: The Prophecy
pxnodes.description: Hekata and her sisters report that they have a prophecy for the player. By delivering 20t of Quartz, they offer the player a look into their crustal ball and tell them the player's future.

pxnodes.name: Black Gold
pxnodes.description: Noting the advanced needs of Envoys, the Grand vizier informs the player that Envoys want to drink Coffee. He wants the player to construct 1 Roasting house and 1 Coffee plantation on one of the player's islands.

pxnodes.name: The struggle continues
pxnodes.description: Phillipe Lamour returns with message from his Lady Marie d'Artois. The fight is still continuing, but the situation is still dire. He asks the player to provide her with 20t of Coffee and 20t of Carpets so that she still has a chance of holding out.

pxnodes.name: The Rescue
pxnodes.description: Seeing the Mining camp, the Grand vizier and Abbess Hildegard urge the player to use the Miners and finally free the Lord from the Assassins.

pxnodes.name: The Bridgehead
pxnodes.description: The Miners need to get on the Island of no return. Al Zahir suggests using the Miners to build a Castle on the island to do so.

pxnodes.name: The Setup
pxnodes.description: Given that the player already has a warehouse on the Island of no Return, Al Zahir orders the player to position the Miners on the island and prepare the rescue mission.

pxnodes.name: The Tunnel
pxnodes.description: After all the preparations, it is now time to order the Miners to rescue the Lord. To do so, the player has to select the Miners and right-click the prison tower and tell the Miners to attack.

pxnodes.name: A suitable Residence
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir notes that the Lord can not be kept in the Castle, so he suggests that the player convert the Castle into a warehouse, where the Lord can be stationed until the player picks him up.

pxnodes.name: Reparation
pxnodes.description: To ensure the structural integrity of the prison tower, the Assassins require 20t of Mosaic and 20t of Clay from the player.

pxnodes.name: Black Assassin's drink
pxnodes.description: The Assassins are working day-in and day-out to repair the tower, however the men are getting tired. Al Rashid asks the player to deliver 20t of Coffee and 20t of Milk to make really good coffee.

pxnodes.name: Free at last!
pxnodes.description: After countless days and nights without any chance of seeing anything else than the prison's walls, Lord Richard Northburgh is on the one hand very happy to see the player, but also determined to stop Kardinal Lucius. He urges the player to bring him to the Emperor so that he can help them in their quest to stop the Kardinal.

pxnodes.name: Hanging by a thread
pxnodes.description: The Emperor is ridden with sickness to his bones. In order to hope for any assistance in defeating the Kardinal, the player has to make sure that the Emperor survives his current condition in the first place.

pxnodes.name: The only hope
pxnodes.description: Searching the books and everything they have, Hildegard and Richard Northburgh find a recipe of a remedy that might be able to cure the Emperor. However, only the witches know of the recipe. The player has to get to them as soon as possible and ask them about their recipe.

pxnodes.name: Witch's curse
pxnodes.description: The witches do know of the recipe, however, a merchant just stole the recipe! The player has to destroy the ship and return the recipe from the sinking ship before bringing it back to the witches. The merchant might already be gone, but the witches cursed the ship, so the player might be able to catch up!

pxnodes.name: Defence of the homeland
pxnodes.description: Phillipe Lamour notes that the situation is looking worse minute by minute for Marie. He asks for volunteers that might be able to help her out.

pxnodes.name: The search for volunteers
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir mentions that settling 300 Nomads and 500 Envoys should be enough to find a group of volunteers for Marie d'Artois.

pxnodes.name: Time is running out
pxnodes.description: Hekata and her sisters require 1 Black pearl and 1 Four juices in order to brew the Essence of life. Both items that are not trivial to procure...

pxnodes.name: The Black Pearl
pxnodes.description: According to Al Zahir, there are legends that the Black Pearl is an artifact somewhere in one of the ruined Towers, which can be found on one of the islands with ruined towers. He also mentions elephant skeletons being close to the tower...

pxnodes.name: An Alchemist's brew
pxnodes.description: The Four juices is an item that Izmir can procure, however, he does not find his ingredients. He requires the player to deliver 1t of Iron ore, 1t of Gold ore, and 1 Silver bar.

pxnodes.name: The red herring
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois' shipyard has been set ablaze by the Kardinal. Phillipe Lamour asks the player to deliver 3 Oriental warships to aid his Lady in this fight.

pxnodes.name: Hope for the Emperor?
pxnodes.description: The Essence of life has been brewed by the witches. Now it is time for the player to deliver the brew to the Emperor and hopefully save his life.

pxnodes.name: Construction contest
pxnodes.description: Kardinal Lucius wants to finish the Imperial Cathedral in order to proceed with his crusade. The player has to finish the Imperial Cathedral before he does in order to stop him!

pxnodes.name: The return of the Noblemen
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh is devastated seeing his island completely ravaged and destroyed. He wishes that the player would restore the island somewhat close to its former glory so that at least 200 Noblemen move back to Cathedral city.

pxnodes.name: Race against time I
pxnodes.description: The Imperial Cathedral is a huge construction undertaking and requires four phases to be completed; the first one is already completed, as the construction site is already placed in Imperial cathedral. For this mission, the player is tasked with completing the second phase of construction before Kardinal Lucius does. Depending on the selected difficulty, the player has  a different time requirement to do so.

pxnodes.name: Supply problems
pxnodes.description: While Cathedral city does have construction material producers, their natural resources seem to have run low. The player is tasked with restoring the Building material Plants' productivities.

pxnodes.name: Tools required
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh notes that while each phase of the Imperial Cathedral's construction requires different building materials, the workers are going to require tools no matter the phase. The Lord proposes to build at least 5 full-functioning Toolmaker's workshops to satisfy the required need of tools during the construction.

pxnodes.name: Lost at Sea
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir notifies the player that one of his ships went missing and guesses that the Kardinal is behind that. He asks the player to bring him 3 Oriental castaways.

pxnodes.name: A friendly favour
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois' island Inglebeck was also hit by Lucius' forces and she requires 30t of Wood and 15t of Tools to start rebuilding her city.

pxnodes.name: Further relief supplies
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois is almost ready to assist the player in assisting them in their construction of the Imperial Cathedral, however, her population is starving and freezing. She asks the player to deliver 20t of Fish and 40t of Linen garments to Inglebeck.

pxnodes.name: The eyes of Lucius
pxnodes.description: Before the player can reach the warehouse of Inglebeck, Marie d'Artois notifies the player that Lucius' spies were sighted in Inglebeck. She does not want to trade as long as spies are in her city and asks the player to help her find the spies.

pxnodes.name: Spies sighted I
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh notifies the player that spies were sighted close to the Imperial Cathedral and the player has to find them before they wreak havoc.

pxnodes.name: Spies sighted II
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh notifies the player that spies were sighted close to the Imperial Cathedral and the player has to find them before they wreak havoc.

pxnodes.name: Spies sighted III
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh notifies the player that spies were sighted close to the Imperial Cathedral and the player has to find them before they wreak havoc.

pxnodes.name: Spies sighted IV
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh notifies the player that spies were sighted close to the Imperial Cathedral and the player has to find them before they wreak havoc.

pxnodes.name: Spies sighted V
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh notifies the player that spies were sighted close to the Imperial Cathedral and the player has to find them before they wreak havoc.

pxnodes.name: Spies sighted VI
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh notifies the player that spies were sighted close to the Imperial Cathedral and the player has to find them before they wreak havoc.

pxnodes.name: Spies sighted VII
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh notifies the player that spies were sighted close to the Imperial Cathedral and the player has to find them before they wreak havoc.

pxnodes.name: Walls for eternity
pxnodes.description: In preparation for the next phase, Lord Richard Northburgh tasks the player with building 5 fully working Stonemason's huts. The player has to use the natural resources of multiple islands to get this quest done.

pxnodes.name: Race against time II
pxnodes.description: With the second construction phase completed, the Lord acknowledges that the Kardinal is also done with the second construction phase. There is no time to lose and the player has to finish the third construction phase before the Kardinal does.

pxnodes.name: The assault
pxnodes.description: One of Al Zahir's ships has been attacked and he requires assistance from the player. Onboard were skilled Master builders who have been injured, so he requires 20t of Bread and 20t of Linen garments to stock up his temporarily constructed outpost with limited resources.

pxnodes.name: Missing
pxnodes.description: Marie d'Artois' visions showed one of her ships sinking and asks the player to look for the ship towards the Northeast of the region.

pxnodes.name: The last contingent I
pxnodes.description: Set on destroying Lucius for what he has done, Marie wants to assist the player in the impending confrontation with Lucius' ships. She requires 40t of Ropes to start construction of a war fleet.

pxnodes.name: The last contingent II
pxnodes.description: Marie can not produce weapons due to the immense destruction of her island and requires the player to deliver 40t of Weapons so that she can add ships to her war fleet.

pxnodes.name: We need glass!
pxnodes.description: In preparation of the last construction phase, Lord Richard Northburgh mentions that this construction phase completely revolves around the windows and therefore proposes to construct 5 completely functional Glass furnaces.

pxnodes.name: Race against time III
pxnodes.description: Only one more construction phase stands between the player and the finished Imperial Cathedral. However, Kardinal Lucius is in hot pursuit and also working on the final construction phase. The player has to be faster than him again, otherwise, everything is lost.

pxnodes.name: Protest from the very top
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir found out that Kardinal Lucius is forcing the Scholars of the Academy and Ibn al Hakim for his evildoings! He does have a plan to stop that, though...

pxnodes.name: Messenger service
pxnodes.description: Al Zahir presents the player a sealed Strongbox that can free Ibn al Hakim from working for Lucius by delivering it to Abbad Jalamid, where Ibn al Hakim and the Scholars reside.

pxnodes.name: Unexpected help
pxnodes.description: After learning about your peculiar situation, Karim offers to procure a flag of Kardinal Lucius so that they can sneak in to deliver the sealed Strongbox to Ibn al Hakim. He does require 15t of Paper and 2000 Gold coins to do so, however.

pxnodes.name: Against the Black Death
pxnodes.description: Lord Richard Northburgh notices that all the inhabitants of Cathedral city became ill and it is an illness similar to the Emperor's. Luckily, Karim has another Essence of Life but requires 10t of Iron as exchange.

pxnodes.name: The end of the Cardinal
pxnodes.description: The player's Imperial Cathedral is finished before the Kardinal's and now it is time to end his shenanigans once and for all.

pxnodes.name: On the Emperor's orders
pxnodes.description: The Emperor has arrived and is not happy with Kardinal Lucius. He orders the player to sink the Kardinal's fleet once and for all.

pxnodes.name: Protection
pxnodes.description: Noting his imminent defeat, Kardinal Lucius sent a few warships to Marie's settlement to take revenge after everything that she has caused. The player is tasked with protecting at least 1 of Marie's ships in Inglebeck.

pxnodes.name: Vengeance
pxnodes.description: The Grand vizier also feels the Kardinal's wrath and requires the player to protect at least 1 of his ships in Al Alin against the Kardinal.

pxnodes.name: Tardy justice
pxnodes.description: The fleet has been sunk, however, there is no sign of Kardinal Lucius. The Emperor wants to bring justice and requires the Kardinal to be delivered to him and urges the player to find the missing Kardinal promptly!

pxnodes.name: Scurvy thieving
pxnodes.description: Spies stole all the wood supplies in Cathedral city. Lord Richard Northburgh tasks the player with filling up the storage with 15t of Wood.

pxnodes.name: Explosion in the mine
pxnodes.description: Lucius' spies blew up the Iron mine in the East of Cathedral city. The Lord asks the player to rebuild the mine.

pxnodes.name: Sabotage at Sea
pxnodes.description: The Kardinal's spies were able to blow up the small trade ship responsible for trading between Cathedral city and Pepperbrook. A replacement trade ship has to be built by the player.

pxnodes.name: Destroyed community
pxnodes.description: The spies were able to destroy the marketplace in Cathedral city's Northwest. Reconstruction is required in order to satisfy the people's need for community.

pxnodes.name: Transportation required
pxnodes.description: The central market building in Carlingham has been blown up by Lucius' spies. Reconstruction is required.

pxnodes.name: Sabotage in the warehouse
pxnodes.description: Lucius' saboteurs destroyed the warehouse in Pepperbrook. Without it, no ship can deliver spices to Cathedral city so the player has to reconstruct it.

pxnodes.name: Attack on the Coast
pxnodes.description: A ship just rammed into the Fisherman's huts in Cathedral city and blew everything up. The Lord tasks the player with rebuilding 4 Fisherman's huts as soon as possible.
